news.title: MIDC allots 400 industrial plots in new Ajang-Ravalgaon industrial estate
news.para: MIDC officials said these 400 units will construct their manufacturing plants in the next two to three years, which will fetch over Rs 1,500 crore of investment and generate employment for over 4,000 people.

news.title: Bombay HC orders Bandra tenant to vacate flat in 'unsafe' building
news.para: The order follows a report by the court-appointed independent structural auditor labelling it as C-1 category, or 'dangerous and unsafe', like the BMC did earlier. The HC also said post handover, the landlord is to demolish the "offending structure and building within three months".

news.title: Indore civic body to sell shops built at PMAY sites
news.para: There are around 200 shops constructed at multi-storey buildings constructed at 15 different locations under the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana, said officials.

news.title: Delhi government to connect all unauthorised colonies with sewer system
news.para: The statement said that under these projects, the Delhi government will conduct a study on newly constructed lakes to assess the groundwater flow. It said that the existing capacity of Rohini Lake No 1 and 2 will also be increased.

news.title: Rising rates set to defer homebuying and opt for rental accommodation
news.para: According to property consultant Knight Frank India, although the interest rate this far has not had a significant impact on sales, with the deterioration of affordability, this could become a factor soon.

news.title: Odisha: EOW arrests Odyssa Homes' director for Rs 20 crore fraud
news.para: Recently, the Bureau of Immigration had issued a look-out circular (LOC) against Panda, director of Odyssa Homes & Commercials Pvt Ltd, suspecting he may flee the country.

news.title: 'Keep a distance from builders', Bombay HC raps BMC
news.para: Tenants of erstwhile Janki Bhuvan, that had been taken up for redevelopment in 2009 by Sanghavi Grih Nirman Pvt Ltd, but had failed to complete it, had then moved high court.

news.title: Gurugram: IIT-Delhi submits Chintels Paradiso tower D's final audit report
news.para: The district administration and department of town and country planning (DTCP), after the cave-in at the Sector 109 society, had ordered an investigation and roped in IIT-Delhi for the structural audit in the highrise’s tower D.

news.title: Lenskart's co-founder buys south Delhi property for Rs 22 crore
news.para: Startup founders and company promoters looking to save on taxes have emerged as the main buyers of super luxury real estate properties after selling shares or stakes in their companies.

news.title: Bengaluru: 18 years on, Arkavathy Layout still lacks power, water supply
news.para: Aggrieved by poor roads and elusive water and power supplies, site owners from all 22 blocks at the layout are planning to protest outside the BDA headquarters at Kumara Park West soon.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body to debate development charges for buildings constructed after 1995
news.para: As per the second, owners of buildings constructed after the year 1995 should pay external development charges (EDC) and those who come to take the TS -1 (no dues) certificate from the civic body should first be asked to clear dues in the building branch.

news.title: Maharashtra government floats global tender for Dharavi redevelopment project
news.para: On Friday, Maharashtra’s Deputy Chief Minister Devendra Fadnavis had announced that the government has already completed the process of granting approvals to this ambitious project and the tendering process required to commence the redevelopment work will be done in the next three months.

news.title: Gandhinagar: Consumer court orders Vidyutnagar Township promoters to compensate buyer
news.para: The case involved a Gandhinagar resident, Ajitsinh Bhatti, who booked a plot with Vidyutnagar Township Pvt Ltd in 2011 and began paying money to its promoters, though there was no clarity on the acquisition of land in absence of any NA permission and NOC from the authorities concerned.

news.title: Savyasachi Infrastructure booked for duping people in Gurugram: Police
news.para: According to a complaint from Ramesh Kumar, a resident of Hisar, more than 20 people had booked the shop-cum-office spaces in the Amaya Green project at sector 3, Farrukhnagar.

news.title: Properties registration in Mumbai up 11% at 8,628 units in Sept: Report
news.para: ​Mumbai city (BMC area) saw property sale registrations of 8,628 units in September 2022 as against 7,804 units in the same month last year and 8,552 units in the previous month, the property consultant said in a statement.
